  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC Asia Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Given that the Fund will co-invest in IFC projects, its development impact will be in line with those of IFC&apos;&apos;s investments, which are tracked using IFC&apos;&apos;s development outcome tracking systems. Expected development impact to be created includes job creation, financial inclusion and creating access to goods and services.  2. The Fund will further enhance and expand IFC&apos;&apos;s development impact by mobilizing additional external capital for high impact investments including investments in frontier countries, and by freeing up economic capital so that IFC can make more investments and thus extend its development reach</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC is proposing to invest in a to-be-established investment vehicle (the &quot;IFC Asia Fund&quot;) with a target size of US$1-1.5 billion, which will mobilize additional capital for co-investments alongside IFC in emerging markets of Asia Pacific region, as defined by IFC. The Fund will be managed by IFC Asset Management Company LLC (AMC).</narrative>
  </description>
